  "title": "ARCHITECTURAL DRAFTER COORDINATOR",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities & Requirements:</p><ul><li>-Proficiency in AutoCAD (Experience in Revit will be advantages)</li><li>-Proficiency in Google Sketch-up</li><li>-Proficient in English, with clear communication skills essential for team collaboration</li><li>-Right attitude with good interpersonal and communication skills.</li><li>-Team player and result-oriented</li><li>-Ability to work independently, as well as part of a team, managing multiple tasks simultaneously.</li><li>-Prepare drawings, detail drawings, and AS-Built drawings using AutoCAD, ensuring accuracy and completeness for submission.</li><li>-Prepare coordination drawings (M&E, P&S with Archi & C&S drawing)\\</li><li>-Update AutoCAD files to reflect the latest layout changes and ensure that references are accurate.</li><li>-Ensure proper revision control of drawing files and documentation.</li><li>-Support project administration tasks including document management</li><li>-Perform other ad-hoc drafting assigned by the Project Management Team to support project needs.</li><li>5.5 days work </li><li>MUST HAVE 3 YEARS EXPERIENCED IN SINGAPORE(Familiar with Nparks, Town Council, HDB projects)</li></ul>",
